
CSS Vs SCSS
CSS is a styling language that lets users create, design, and style various web pages.
    CSS : Cascading Style Sheet is the basically the scripting language
    We generally use CSS in the JavaScript and HTML languages.


SCSS is a special file type in a SASS program that one needs to write in the Ruby language.
    SCSS stands for the Sassy Cascading Style Sheets
    SCSS contains all the features of CSS and contains more features that are not present in CSS which makes it a good choice for developers to use it.
    We generally use the SCSS in the Ruby language.